## 6. Methodology and Limitations

### Scraping

- **Platform:** CFTC Public Comments Portal (comments.cftc.gov)
- **Docket:** {{ docket_id }}
- **Coverage:** {{ stats.total_submissions }} submissions crawled of {{ stats.total_submissions }} listed
- **Attachment downloads:** {{ stats.attachment_downloads_ok }} successful / {{ stats.attachment_downloads_failed }} failed

### Text Extraction

- HTML body extraction: BeautifulSoup
- PDF extraction: PyMuPDF (primary), pdfplumber (fallback)
- DOCX extraction: python-docx
- Submissions with no extractable text: {{ stats.extraction_failed }}
- Partial extractions (e.g. scanned PDFs): logged separately

### Deduplication

- **Method:** SHA-256 exact hash + MinHash LSH (threshold {{ dedup_threshold }}, {{ minhash_perms }} permutations)
- **Campaign threshold:** groups of ≥ {{ campaign_min }} identical/near-identical submissions flagged
- All dedup decisions are recorded with `dedup_method` and `similarity_score` fields

### LLM Analysis

- **Model:** {{ llm_model }}
- **Prompt version:** {{ prompt_version }}
- **Schema:** Pydantic-validated JSON with automatic retry (max 3 attempts)
- **Limitation:** LLM may misclassify stance for mixed or ambiguous comments
- **Limitation:** Text truncated at 12,000 characters for very long submissions

### Clustering

- **Embedding model:** all-MiniLM-L6-v2
- **Algorithm:** HDBSCAN (min_cluster_size={{ hdbscan_min_cluster }})
- **Noise points** (unclustered): {{ stats.noise_submissions }} submissions
- Cluster labels are auto-generated and may be overridden by analysts in the UI

